All MATLAB/LAMMPS/FORTRAN/Python source code for the publication: 
Simulating precursor steps for fibril formation in methylcellulose solutions (Physical Review Materials 3 (5), 055601)

For bug fixes/more details, please contact vsethura@umn.edu

Data repository: https://conservancy.umn.edu/handle/11299/202793
Video repository: https://conservancy.umn.edu/handle/11299/202217


MATLAB file details: All codes are compatible with M-2017b.
1) genplane.m -- To generate best fit plane
2) kappa_ana.m -- To compute the eigenvalues and shape anisotropy factors (global and individual)
Required files: pl_indkappa.m, pl_indeig.m, analyze_kappa.m, read_analyze_indeig.m
3) plot_generic_kappa.m -- To create colormaps of shape anisotropy factors. 
Use consolidate_eigendata.m prior to using this for each case
